  - We can recognise that the area of region $U$ can be found by subtracting the area under the curve from $A$ to $C$ from the red dashed rectangle, this is shown below

  ![SkillUpp Image](https://assets.revisionvillage.com/public/question/51c5c963-7f0e-489b-8337-0d8c9be7a46a/images/87de2b7d-c023-4705-ba3c-3490c4ad34d0/AA1160_a2.JPEG)


  Hence

  $$
  \begin{align*}
      A_U&=6-\int_{2}^{4}f(x)\,dx\tag*{\textbf{M1}}\\[12pt]  
