  $$

  Using the answer from part (b) and remembering that for definite integrals the constant $C$ cancels out

  $$
  \begin{align*}
      &=6-\left[\tfrac{1}{12}(x-2)^3+2x\right]_{2}^{4}\\[12pt]
      &=6-\left[\left(\tfrac{1}{12}(4-2)^3+2\times 4\right)-\left(\tfrac{1}{12}(2-2)^3+2\times 2\right)\right]\\[12pt]
      &=6-\left[\left(\tfrac{8}{12}+8\right)-4\right]\\[12pt]
      &=6-\left(\tfrac{2}{3}+4\right)\\[12pt]
      &=\tfrac{4}{3} \tag*{\textbf{A1}}
  \end{align*}
  $$

  We can find the area of $L$ in a similar way

